Amazing Korean BBQ

The spicy pork belly is to DIE for. Everything is delicious,  fresh, and satisfying. I feel bad about those who reviewed them for poor service because that has never been the case the ~5 times I've visited, different days and times and wait staff. I don't have a red carpet rolled out for me at every restaurant, nor do I expect it. I think what people are picking up on, and are trying to say is that they do not have a host. Everyone plays a part and helps take orders, serve, make and give drinks, and importantly for Korean BBQ- replacing the hot plates when someone accidentally burns something, or simply over time as sauces build up & cook. The only complaint I've ever had was that at night, the music gets very loud....this is coming from a 1/2 deaf girl! I'm not sure if they're covering up a karaoke place next door or trying to accommodate the bustling group conversations that happen over this type of dining, but it's nonexistent during the day and doesn't impact HOW DELICIOUS the food is. I really hope they address this since I'm not the only or first one to review that detail...and it honestly does deter me from going when I want a more relaxing night out. For all-you-can eat, it is a GREAT PRICE, GOOD VALUE. I always get the top (more money, but not by much so worth it based on your preference) option. Most outrageously priced item is the soju. They sell it for literally 3× the price I buy it at Total Wine or 2× more at my favorite hot pot place... not going to deter me from returning though.🙂 Parking is in the back in a shared big lot which was the only "tough" part of locating it by car..

During this visit with my wife, I pointed out to our waitress that there was a bug still crawling around in our salad. So she takes the salad aside and as she is walking away, turns back and asked if we wanted another one. We said no and there were no further exchange of words with her. My wife was ready to bolt out of there but I asked her to stay. So we didn't leave and decided to give them a chance with the rest of the food as we were already committed. After some time, our waitress comes back with our order but we were missing a couple of items. We started eating and waited for the rest of the order but she never came back around after that. Nearly all of the wait staff were standing in their own little group near the cash register chatting amongst themselves and never  came to check in on us except for when one of them came by to change the heating plate. The attention to customers service has deteriorated since I first went there. We may give them another chance but highly doubt that we'll be going to Sura anytime soon if at all.

Not impressed.  I have not been back.  I went for lunch with my kids, toddlers.  They are usually pretty adventuresome for their ages.  The behavior of the staff and service was just plain weird.  They acted like they expected us to steal food or something.  It was like they were penny pinching. They told us that we must eat all of our food before we could order something else.  At first I thought it was just a language barrier, but the nervousness of the wait staff made for a very unpleasant atmosphere.  If that was not enough, the meat was very bland. The bean sauce wasn't that flavorful to help the unseasoned meat.  The garlic sauce was okay, but they could really use more variety of more flavorful sauces.  Perhaps the food is more traditional Korean than I am used to.  There were a lot of Asians, probably Koreans, dining there. I have just had better, more flavorful bbq.  I seriously wanted to ask for some salt!  I ordered chicken for the kids and the beef tongue for me, which I normally really enjoy.  The tongue was served frozen, which was also a surprise, and was very bland once cooked.  I was underwhelmed to say the least.  I thought it was very, very expensive since the food was so underwhelming.  The whole experience just wasn't worth the $$ for me.

Really nice place for AYCE Korean BBQ. They have 2 menus to chose from, either A, cheaper one with less options, or B, a slightly more expensive one that includes the first menu's options and more. My friends and I went for option A, and we loved the spicy pork, prime brisket, and pork belly. I felt like option A had plenty of options for us, with different meats, soup, scallion pancake, etc. They also give you many side dishes as usual and you can ask for rice. The downsides were that there were no exhaust pipes or fans or anything so the restaurant felt/smelled very smoky as food cooked, and it was difficult to call the waiter over and get service (as with many AYCE restaurants).
